sentences.english: Geithner flew to Beijing to meet Wang at the airport.
sentences.chinese: 蓋特納便飛往北京在機場與王岐山會面。

sentences.english: China's vice premier Wang Qishan started up the service.
sentences.chinese: 中國副總理王岐山啓動了服務儀式。

sentences.english: There emerged 36 kinds of intonation patterns of sound cluster of double characters group in Qishan dialect.
sentences.chinese: 岐山方言語音中兩字組連讀共產生了36種連讀調式。

sentences.english: I want to thank State CouncilorDai and Vice-Premier Wang for their very warm hospitality.
sentences.chinese: 感謝國務委員戴秉國和副總理王岐山非常熱情的接待。

sentences.english: Wang will be closed for his vassal to the west of Shaanxi Qishan land grant him.
sentences.chinese: 平王便封他爲諸侯，將陝西岐山以西的土地賜予他。

sentences.english: Qishan County lies on the west of Fufeng County.
sentences.chinese: 岐山縣位於扶風縣的西面。

sentences.english: Wang hailed the commitment of Kansai to promoting Sino-Japanese friendship and exchanges.
sentences.chinese: 王岐山對關西地區長期致力於中日友好往來表示讚賞。

sentences.english: Wang first of all extended congratulations on the success of the dialogue.
sentences.chinese: 王岐山首先對中美省州長對話的成功舉行表示祝賀。
